flowRoot.flowPara: Debian is a free operating system (OS) for your computer. An operating system is the set of basic programs and utilities that make your computer run. Debian uses the Linux kernel (the kernel is the core of an OS), but most of the basic OS tools come from the GNU project. Thus we refer to Debian as a Debian GNU/Linux operating system, giving credit to all its originators. Debian GNU/Linux provides much more than just the OS - a wide range of application software is included too. It comes with a total of over 29000 packages, precompiled software bundled up in a nice format for easy installation on your machine.
